article_title: U.S. Import Prices Fall 0.1% in June
article_text:
WASHINGTON—Prices for imported goods fell in June, a reminder of the strong dollar and soft overseas growth that are constraining the U.S. economy.

Import prices decreased a seasonally adjusted 0.1% in June from a month earlier, the Labor Department said Tuesday. Economists surveyed by The Wall Street Journal had expected import prices to rise...
